{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772178958392,"sessionID":"ses_361eb8b90ffeYmwBV3N68Ex01B","part":{"id":"prt_c9e18e6cf0018HQALcX0S3aGFy","sessionID":"ses_361eb8b90ffeYmwBV3N68Ex01B","messageID":"msg_c9e18de090011LWjtFZNYTVQ6G","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_013HEnjCYuCoPEKETDXpiVdo","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/module-catalog.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/mat/dev/farsight/agent-framework/spec/module-catalog.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Module Catalog\n2: \n3: > Complete inventory of all source modules in the super-ralph agent framework,\n4: > grouped by domain.\n5: \n6: **Source examined at commit:** `ecc95c0` (2026-02-27)\n7: \n8: ## Coverage Key\n9: \n10: | Status | Meaning |\n11: | --- | --- |\n12: | `covered` | A detailed spec file exists in `spec/`. |\n13: | `partial` | Spec exists but is incomplete or draft. |\n14: | `todo` | No spec file yet. |\n15: \n16: ## Domains\n17: \n18: The nineteen source modules in `src/` fall into five domains:\n19: \n20: 1. [Phases](#phases) — Top-level command orchestration (3 modules)\n21: 2. [Engine](#engine) — Core iteration loop and lifecycle (1 module)\n22: 3. [Integrations](#integrations) — External service adapters (3 modules)\n23: 4. [Infrastructure](#infrastructure) — Cross-cutting support utilities (9 modules)\n24: 5. [CLI Entry Point](#cli-entry-point) — Argument parsing and dispatch (1 module)\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Phases\n29: \n30: Phase modules implement the three top-level commands. Each module calls\n31: `runPhaseLoop` from the engine and supplies phase-specific callbacks for\n32: selecting work, building prompts, and handling results.\n33: \n34: | Module | Path | Responsibility | Status |\n35: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n36: | Forward | `src/forward.ts` | Picks the highest-priority ready bead, renders a prompt, and drives the engine until all epic beads are closed. | `todo` |\n37: | Decompose | `src/decompose.ts` | Creates an epic via `br`, then iteratively prompts the agent to read a spec file and produce beads from it. | `todo` |\n38: | Reverse | `src/reverse.ts` | Runs either an interactive SSE session (human-driven Q&A) or an autonomous loop that refines a Markdown spec document. | `todo` |\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## Engine\n43: \n44: The engine module owns the generic iteration loop shared by all three phases.\n45: \n46: | Module | Path | Responsibility | Status |\n47: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n48: | Engine | `src/engine.ts` | Drives the select-prompt-execute-evaluate loop; manages retries, error strategy, event emission, run tracking, and timeouts. | `todo` |\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## Integrations\n53: \n54: Integration modules wrap external services and tools behind typed interfaces\n55: used by the engine and phase modules.\n56: \n57: | Module | Path | Responsibility | Status |\n58: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n59: | OpenCode adapter | `src/opencode.ts` | Manages OpenCode server lifecycle, session creation, real-time SSE prompt streaming, and result extraction. | `todo` |\n60: | Interactive session | `src/interactive.ts` | Handles the interactive reverse mode: subscribes to SSE events, intercepts questions, and renders them via `@clack/prompts` or mock answers. | `todo` |\n61: | Bead integration | `src/beads.ts` | Thin adapter around the `br` CLI: spawns child processes, parses JSON output, and returns typed `BeadInfo` objects. | `todo` |\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## Infrastructure\n66: \n67: Infrastructure modules provide cross-cutting support — configuration, templating,\n68: persistence, event routing, and utilities — consumed by the engine and phases.\n69: \n70: | Module | Path | Responsibility | Status |\n71: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n72: | Types | `src/types.ts` | Central type definitions: all shared interfaces and type aliases used across the codebase. | `todo` |\n73: | Config | `src/config.ts` | Loads and merges `.super-ralph/config.toml` with defaults; resolves AI model selection by bead labels or CLI override. | `todo` |\n74: | Template | `src/template.ts` | Loads and renders Handlebars `.hbs` prompt templates stored in `.super-ralph/`. | `todo` |\n75: | Output parser | `src/output-parser.ts` | Accumulates raw SSE event lines and display text during a session; caps total size at 250,000 characters. | `todo` |\n76: | Run state | `src/run-state.ts` | Persists per-run artifacts: timestamped run directory, live `session.json`, JSONL event log, and per-iteration transcripts. | `todo` |\n77: | Run status | `src/run-status.ts` | Read-only companion to run state; resolves a run reference and reads back session state, event counts, and transcript paths. | `todo` |\n78: | Progress | `src/progress.ts` | Appends human-readable Markdown progress entries to `progress.md` after each iteration; reads recent entries back for agent context. | `todo` |\n79: | Skills | `src/skills.ts` | Resolves a skill name or file path to its Markdown content; supports built-in skills and arbitrary user-supplied paths. | `todo` |\n80: | Timeout | `src/timeout.ts` | Races a promise against a deadline; rejects with a custom error message if the timeout elapses first. | `todo` |\n81: | Init | `src/init.ts` | Scaffolds a new project: creates `.super-ralph/`, copies templates, writes `config.toml`, installs the OpenCode plugin, and runs `br init`. | `todo` |\n82: | Events | `src/events.ts` | Defines the engine event union type, a lightweight pub/sub emitter, and a default console renderer for terminal output. | `todo` |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## CLI Entry Point\n87: \n88: | Module | Path | Responsibility | Status |\n89: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n90: | Index | `src/index.ts` | CLI entry point: parses command-line arguments and dispatches to `forward`, `decompose`, `reverse`, `init`, `status`, or `doctor`. | `todo` |\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## Detailed Spec Files\n95: \n96: No detailed module spec files exist yet. All entries above are `todo`. As\n97: specs are written, this table will be updated to link each module entry to\n98: its `spec/<module-name>.md` file and the status column will advance to\n99: `partial` or `covered`.\n100: \n101: | Spec File | Module | Path |\n102: | --- | --- | --- |\n103: | _(none yet)_ | — | — |\n\n(End of file - total 103 lines)\n</content>","title":"spec/module-catalog.md","metadata":{"preview":"# Module Catalog\n\n> Complete inventory of all source modules in the super-ralph agent framework,\n> grouped by domain.\n\n**Source examined at commit:** `ecc95c0` (2026-02-27)\n\n## Coverage Key\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n| --- | --- |\n| `covered` | A detailed spec file exists in `spec/`. |\n| `partial` | Spec exists but is incomplete or draft. |\n| `todo` | No spec file yet. |\n\n## Domains\n\nThe nineteen source modules in `src/` fall into five domains:\n\n1. [Phases](#phases) — Top-level command orchestration (3 modules)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1772178958388,"end":1772178958391}}}}
