      "errorMessage": "task_id: ses_361eb634fffeoQ0iCX6gk63ynU (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Here is the comprehensive architectural analysis:\n\n---\n\n# Super-Ralph: Comprehensive Architecture Analysis\n\n## 1. Overview and Project Identity\n\n**Super-Ralph** is a CLI-driven, AI-assisted software development lifecycle (SDLC) framework. Its stated goal is to be a \"unified SDLC framework\" that combines three external systems:\n\n- **Superpowers** (structured intake/design methodology)\n- **OpenCode SDK** (`@opencode-ai/sdk`) — an AI coding agent server\n- **Beads** (`br` CLI) — a dependency-aware task tracker\n\nThe core metaphor is the **Ralph Loop**: `SELECT -> PROMPT -> EXECUTE -> EVALUATE`, applied to three sequential phases that transform raw ideas into shipped code.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Directory Structure and Major Domains\n\n```\nagent-framework/\n├── src/                    # All TypeScript source (19 files, ~1,800 LOC)\n│   ├── index.ts            # CLI entry point + argument parsing\n│   ├── engine.ts           # Universal phase-loop runner\n│   ├── forward.ts          # Phase: beads -> code\n│   ├── decompose.ts        # Phase: spec -> beads\n│   ├── reverse.ts          # Phase: input -> spec\n│   ├── interactive.ts      # Interactive (interview) session handler\n│   ├── opencode.ts         # OpenCode SDK wrapper + SSE streaming\n│   ├── beads.ts            # br CLI wrapper + BeadInfo mapper\n│   ├── config.ts           # TOML config loader + model resolution\n│   ├── template.ts         # Handlebars template loader/renderer\n│   ├── skills.ts           # Skill file loader (feature/bug/hotfix/refactor)\n│   ├── events.ts           # EngineEvent type union + EngineEventEmitter\n│   ├── run-state.ts        # Per-run artifact writer (session.json, events.jsonl)\n│   ├── run-status.ts       # Read-back of run artifacts for `status` command\n│   ├── progress.ts         # progress.md read/write\n│   ├── output-parser.ts    # StreamCapture (display + raw SSE buffers)\n│   ├── timeout.ts          # Promise.race-based timeout utility\n│   ├── init.ts             # `super-ralph init` scaffolding\n│   └── types.ts            # All shared TypeScript interfaces\n├── templates/              # Per-project scaffolding templates\n│   ├── forward.hbs         # Handlebars prompt template: forward phase\n│   ├── decompose.hbs       # Handlebars prompt template: decompose phase\n│   ├── reverse.hbs         # Handlebars prompt template: reverse phase\n│   ├── agents.md           # AGENTS.md template (agent instructions)\n│   ├── intake-checklist.md # Growing intake checklist template\n│   └── super-ralph-config.toml  # Default config template\n├── skills/                 # Built-in question banks for reverse phase\n│   ├── feature.md\n│   ├── bug.md\n│   ├── hotfix.md\n│   └── refactor.md\n├── .opencode/\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── super-ralph.js  # OpenCode plugin: registers task_complete tool\n├── tests/\n│   ├── unit/               # Bun unit tests (run-artifacts, mock-answers)\n│   ├── e2e-*.sh            # Shell-based E2E tests (dry-run + live)\n│   └── fixtures/           # Tiny project fixtures for tests\n├── docs/\n│   ├── plans/              # Design documents (19 files) — architectural history\n│   └── reference/          # Reference docs: ralph-loop-architecture, run-artifacts\n├── dist/                   # Built output (bun build)\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── install.sh / uninstall.sh\n└── README.md\n```\n\n**Major domains:**\n\n| Domain | Files | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| CLI/Commands | `index.ts`, `init.ts` | Argument parsing, command dispatch, `doctor` |\n| Phase Engine | `engine.ts` | Universal loop runner |\n| Phases | `forward.ts`, `decompose.ts`, `reverse.ts` | Phase-specific callbacks |\n| OpenCode Integration | `opencode.ts`, `interactive.ts` | Server lifecycle, session management, SSE streaming |\n| Beads Integration | `beads.ts` | Spawns `br` CLI, parses JSON output |\n| Configuration | `config.ts`, `types.ts` | TOML config, model resolution |\n| Templating | `template.ts`, `skills.ts` | Handlebars rendering, skill file loading |\n| Observability | `events.ts`, `run-state.ts`, `run-status.ts`, `progress.ts`, `output-parser.ts` | Event emission, artifact writing, transcript capture |\n| Utilities | `timeout.ts` | Promise timeout wrapper |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Entry Points\n\n### Primary CLI Entry Point\n**`src/index.ts`** — shebang `#!/usr/bin/env bun`. Installed as a shell wrapper script that calls `bun run ~/.super-ralph-cli/src/index.ts \"$@\"` (via `install.sh`).\n\nThe `bin` field in `package.json` points to `./dist/index.js` for the built distribution, but development uses `bun run src/index.ts` directly.\n\n### Command Dispatch\n`index.ts` implements a manual argument parser (`parseArgs`) that produces `{ command, positionals, flags }`. The `switch` at the bottom dispatches to:\n\n| Command | Function | File |\n|---|---|---|\n| `forward` / `run` (alias) | `cmdForward()` -> `runForward()` | `forward.ts` |\n| `decompose` | `cmdDecompose()` -> `runDecompose()` | `decompose.ts` |\n| `reverse` | `cmdReverse()` -> `runReverse()` | `reverse.ts` |\n| `init` | `runInit()` | `init.ts` |\n| `status` | `cmdStatus()` | inline in `index.ts` |\n| `doctor` | `cmdDoctor()` | inline in `index.ts` |\n| `help` | `printUsage()` | inline in `index.ts` |\n\n### Boolean flags (`BOOLEAN_FLAGS`): `dry-run`, `interactive`, `fix` — these never consume the next argument.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Core Abstractions and Major Interfaces\n\n### `types.ts` — Shared Type Definitions\n\n```typescript\n// Task unit from the beads tracker\ninterface BeadInfo {\n  id: string; title: string; description?: string;\n  status: \"open\" | \"in_progress\" | \"closed\";\n  labels: string[];  // includes \"area:frontend-design\" etc.\n  priority: number;  // 0=critical, 4=backlog\n  dependsOn: string[]; blocks: string[];\n  type?: string; parentId?: string;\n}\n\n// Runtime configuration (from config.toml)\ninterface LoopConfig {\n  engine: { timeout_minutes, inactivity_timeout_seconds, iteration_delay_ms, strategy, max_retries };\n  opencode: { url };\n  cli: { path };\n  models: { default, [alias]: string };\n  modelsAreas: { [areaName]: providerModel };\n  reverse: { output_dir };\n  decompose: { include_review, include_bugscan, include_audit };\n}\n\n// Result of a single loop iteration\ninterface IterationResult {\n  iteration, beadId, beadTitle, status, reason, model, duration,\n  cost?, tokens?, filesChanged?, transcriptPath?\n}\n\n// What an agent signals via task_complete tool\ninterface CompletionResult {\n  status: \"complete\" | \"phase_done\" | \"blocked\" | \"failed\" | \"stalled\" | \"timeout\" | \"error\";\n  reason?: string;\n}\n\n// Aggregate across all iterations\ninterface LoopResult { completed, failed, skipped, totalTime, maxIterations, iterations }\n\n// Flags common to all three phases\ninterface PhaseFlags { dryRun, maxIterations?, modelOverride?, attach? }\ninterface ForwardFlags   extends PhaseFlags { epicId }\ninterface DecomposeFlags extends PhaseFlags { specPath, epicTitle? }\ninterface ReverseFlags   extends PhaseFlags { inputs[], outputDir?, skill?, interactive?, answersFile? }\n```\n\n### `engine.ts` — The Universal Phase Loop\n\nThe central abstraction is `PhaseCallbacks` — an interface every phase implements to hook into the generic loop runner:\n\n```typescript\ninterface PhaseIteration {\n  prompt: string;\n  model: { providerID: string; modelID: string };\n  sessionTitle: string;\n  iterationLabel: string;\n  beadId?: string;\n  systemPrompt?: string;\n}\n\ninterface PhaseCallbacks {\n  setup(config, dryRun): Promise<{ maxIterations: number; description: string }>;\n  nextIteration(config, iteration): Promise<PhaseIteration | null>;\n  handleResult(result: CompletionResult, iteration): Promise<boolean>;\n}\n```\n\n`runPhaseLoop(projectDir, callbacks, flags, onEvent?)` is the single generic runner used by all three phases.\n\n### `events.ts` — Typed Event Bus\n\n`EngineEvent` is a discriminated union of 13 event types. `EngineEventEmitter` is a simple publish/subscribe with `on(listener)` returning a detach function. Three listeners are always attached when a loop runs:\n\n1. `attachDefaultConsoleRenderer` — prints to stdout\n2. `runTracker.recordEvent` — writes to `events.jsonl` + updates `session.json`\n3. Optional external `onEvent` callback (for testing or TUI integration)\n\n### `opencode.ts` — Server and Session Management\n\nKey types and functions:\n- `ServerHandle` — `{ client: OpencodeClient, url: string, close: () => void }`\n- `PromptResult` — `{ completion, cost, tokens, filesChanged, rawOutput, displayOutput }`\n- `startServer()` — calls `createOpencode({ port: 0 })` (random port), verifies via `client.session.list()`\n- `connectToServer(url)` — for `--attach` mode, wraps existing server\n- `createSession(client, title)` — thin wrapper around SDK\n- `runPrompt(client, sessionId, prompt, model, systemPrompt, serverUrl, inactivityMs)` — the main SSE event loop (described in detail in section 7)\n- `extractCompletion(parts)` — scans session message parts for a `task_complete` tool call\n- `checkBrokenSymlinks(opts)` — scans `~/.config/opencode/plugins` and `commands` for broken symlinks (defensive startup check)\n\n### `run-state.ts` — `RunTracker` Interface\n\n```typescript\ninterface RunTracker {\n  runId: string;\n  runDir: string;\n  recordEvent(event: EngineEvent): void;\n  writeIterationTranscript(iteration, label, rawOutput?, displayOutput?): string | undefined;\n  finalize(status: \"completed\" | \"failed\"): void;\n}\n```\n\n`startRunTracker()` creates the directory tree and returns a closure-based `RunTracker`. The `runId` is `${Date.now()}-${random6chars}`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Runtime Lifecycle: Initialize, Run, Shut Down\n\n### Phase Lifecycle (all three phases share this)\n\n```\n1. CLI parses args -> dispatches to cmdForward/cmdDecompose/cmdReverse\n2. Phase function calls runPhaseLoop(projectDir, callbacks, flags)\n3. engine.ts: runPhaseLoop()\n   a. Creates EngineEventEmitter, attaches console renderer\n   b. Calls callbacks.setup(config, dryRun) to get maxIterations + description\n   c. Calls startRunTracker() -> creates .super-ralph/runs/<runId>/\n   d. Emits loop.description\n   e. If dryRun: iterates nextIteration() without executing, emits dry_run events, returns\n   f. If flags.attach: connectToServer(url); else startServer() (spawns ephemeral opencode)\n   g. Emits server.started or server.attached\n   h. Main loop (while iteration < maxIterations):\n      i.   callbacks.nextIteration(config, n) -> PhaseIteration | null\n           - null means \"nothing left to do\", breaks loop\n      ii.  Emits iteration.started\n      iii. createSession(server.client, sessionTitle)\n      iv.  Emits iteration.session_created\n      v.   withTimeout(runPrompt(...), timeout_minutes * 60000)\n           - SSE streaming loop runs inside runPrompt\n           - inactivity watchdog polls every 10s\n           - heartbeat log every 30s\n      vi.  runTracker.writeIterationTranscript(...)\n      vii. appendProgress(projectDir, iteration, result) -> .super-ralph/progress.md\n      viii.callbacks.handleResult(result, iteration) -> shouldContinue bool\n      ix.  Based on result.status:\n           - \"complete\" or \"phase_done\": completed++, emit iteration.completed\n           - \"blocked\": skipped++, emit iteration.blocked\n           - \"failed\"/\"error\"/\"stalled\"/\"timeout\":\n             * strategy=\"retry\" and retries < max_retries: iteration--, retryCount++\n             * strategy=\"abort\": failed++, break\n             * strategy=\"skip\": failed++, continue\n      x.   if !shouldContinue: break\n      xi.  Sleep iteration_delay_ms\n   i. Emits loop.completed\n   j. runTracker.finalize(\"completed\" | \"failed\")\n   k. finally: cleanup (close server, detach listeners, finalize tracker if not done)\n4. Returns LoopResult { completed, failed, skipped, totalTime, iterations[] }\n5. index.ts: if result.failed > 0 -> process.exit(1)\n```\n\n### Initialization (`super-ralph init`)\n\n`runInit(projectDir)`:\n1. Creates `.super-ralph/` directory\n2. Copies 5 template files from `templates/` (skips if already exist)\n3. Creates `.super-ralph/config.toml` with auto-detected `cli.path`\n4. Installs `.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js` (the `task_complete` tool plugin) and runs `bun install` in `.opencode/`\n5. Creates `tasks/` directory\n6. Runs `br init` if `.beads/` doesn't exist\n7. Creates or updates root `AGENTS.md` with a reference to `.super-ralph/AGENTS.md`\n\n### Shutdown\n\nServer is always closed in a `finally` block in `runPhaseLoop`. `RunTracker.finalize()` is called with `\"failed\"` if an exception exits before normal finalization. Interactive sessions that time out attempt a best-effort `v2Client.session.abort()` before throwing.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Cross-Domain Interaction Patterns\n\n### How the three phases communicate\nThe phases are **composable but decoupled**. They communicate only through the filesystem and the `br` CLI:\n\n```\nreverse -> writes spec files to docs/specs/ or tasks/\ndecompose -> reads spec file (--spec path), writes beads to .beads/ via br create\nforward -> reads beads from .beads/ via br ready/show, writes code files + commits\n```\n\n### Phase -> Engine (Callback Injection)\n\nEach phase constructs a `PhaseCallbacks` object literal and passes it to `runPhaseLoop`. The engine is completely phase-agnostic. This is a strategy/callback pattern, not inheritance.\n\n### Engine -> OpenCode (HTTP/SSE)\n\nThe engine calls `createSession` then `runPrompt` (both in `opencode.ts`). `runPrompt` uses two SDK clients:\n- **v2 client** (`createV2Client`) — for `promptAsync()` (non-blocking) and SSE event subscription\n- **v1 client** (the `OpencodeClient` from `ServerHandle`) — for `session.messages()` and `session.diff()` after idle\n\n### Engine -> Beads (Subprocess)\n\n`beads.ts` wraps `Bun.spawn([\"br\", ...args])`, capturing stdout as JSON. It filters log lines before the JSON start (`[` or `{`). All beads operations are pure async subprocess calls — no direct filesystem access to `.beads/`.\n\n### Engine -> Filesystem\n\nThree write paths:\n1. `.super-ralph/progress.md` — appended by `appendProgress()` after each iteration\n2. `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/session.json` and `.super-ralph/session.json` — written by `RunTracker.recordEvent()` and `finalize()`\n3. `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/events.jsonl` — appended by `RunTracker.recordEvent()`\n4. `.super-ralph/runs/<runId>/iterations/*.log` — written by `RunTracker.writeIterationTranscript()`\n\n### Plugin -> OpenCode (task_complete tool)\n\n`.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js` uses `@opencode-ai/plugin` to register a custom tool called `task_complete`. OpenCode discovers this plugin when the server starts and makes the tool available to every agent session. The agent calls `task_complete({ status, reason })` as its final action. The engine detects this by scanning `session.messages()` after idle for a `part.type === \"tool\" && part.tool === \"task_complete\"` entry.\n\n### Interactive Mode (reverse phase only)\n\nFor interactive reverse sessions, `reverse.ts` bypasses `runPhaseLoop` entirely and calls `runInteractiveSession()` from `interactive.ts` directly. This uses:\n- `createInteractiveClient(url)` — returns a v2 `OpencodeClient` \n- `@clack/prompts` — renders `question.asked` SSE events as terminal UI (single-select, multi-select, text)\n- `question.reply({ requestID, answers })` — sends user's answer back to the agent\n- `question.reject()` — if user presses Ctrl+C\n\nMock answers (`--answers <path>`) bypass clack entirely via `loadMockAnswers()` / `renderMockAnswer()` for automated testing.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Configuration and Environment Setup\n\n### Config File: `.super-ralph/config.toml`\n\nLoaded by `loadConfig(projectDir)` which merges with `DEFAULT_CONFIG`. The TOML structure:\n\n```toml\n[engine]\ntimeout_minutes = 30          # Hard timeout per iteration (all phases)\ninactivity_timeout_seconds = 180  # Inactivity watchdog (no events for N seconds)\niteration_delay_ms = 2000     # Sleep between iterations\nstrategy = \"retry\"            # retry | skip | abort on failure\nmax_retries = 3\n\n[opencode]\nurl = \"http://localhost:4096\"  # Used by --attach mode\n\n[cli]\npath = \"/abs/path/to/src/index.ts\"  # Set by init; used by doctor\n\n[models]\ndefault = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n\n[models.areas]\nfrontend-design = \"google/gemini-2.5-pro\"\nbackend = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\nreview = \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\"\n\n[reverse]\noutput_dir = \"docs/specs\"\n\n[decompose]\ninclude_review = true\ninclude_bugscan = true\ninclude_audit = true\n```\n\n### Model Resolution (`config.ts::resolveModel`)\n\nThree-level priority:\n1. `flags.modelOverride` (CLI `--model`)\n2. `bead.labels.find(l => l.startsWith(\"area:\"))` -> lookup in `config.modelsAreas`\n3. `config.models.default`\n\nResult is split on `/` to produce `{ providerID, modelID }`.\n\n### Environment Variable\n- `SUPER_RALPH_DEBUG=1` — enables verbose SSE event logging to stderr in `opencode.ts`\n- `SUPER_RALPH_REPO_URL` / `SUPER_RALPH_HOME` / `SUPER_RALPH_BIN_DIR` — install script overrides\n\n### Per-Project Files\n\nAfter `super-ralph init`, a project gets:\n```\n.super-ralph/\n  AGENTS.md               # Framework instructions for any AI reading the project\n  config.toml             # Runtime config\n  forward.hbs             # Prompt template (customizable per project)\n  decompose.hbs           # Prompt template\n  reverse.hbs             # Prompt template\n  intake-checklist.md     # Accumulated intake learnings\n  progress.md             # Written at runtime per iteration\n  session.json            # Mirror of latest run state\n  runs/\n    <runId>/\n      session.json\n      events.jsonl\n      iterations/\n        001-<label>.log\n.opencode/\n  plugins/\n    super-ralph.js        # Provides task_complete to OpenCode agents\n  package.json\n.beads/                   # Beads workspace (managed by br CLI)\ntasks/                    # Spec files from reverse phase (legacy location)\nAGENTS.md                 # Root AGENTS.md (updated to reference .super-ralph/AGENTS.md)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Key Data Flows and Processing Pipelines\n\n### Pipeline 1: Reverse (input -> spec)\n\n**Interactive mode:**\n```\nUser invokes: super-ralph reverse [inputs...] [--skill feature] [--interactive]\n  -> reverse.ts::runInteractive()\n     -> loadConfig(), loadTemplate(\"reverse.hbs\"), loadSkill(flags.skill)\n     -> Optionally loadMockAnswers() for test mode\n     -> startServer() or connectToServer() -> ServerHandle\n     -> createInteractiveClient(url) [v2 SDK]\n     -> v2Client.session.create() -> sessionId\n     -> startRunTracker() -> RunTracker\n     -> withTimeout(runInteractiveSession(...))\n        -> v2Client.event.subscribe() [SSE stream]\n        -> v2Client.session.promptAsync({sessionID, model, parts: [prompt], system})\n        -> Event loop:\n           message.part.delta -> StreamCapture.addDisplayText() + stdout.write()\n           message.part.updated (tool) -> toolStatusText + stdout\n           question.asked -> handleQuestions() -> @clack/prompts -> question.reply()\n           session.idle -> break\n           session.error -> break\n        -> gatherResults(): scan session.messages for task_complete, sum cost/tokens, get diff\n     -> runTracker.writeIterationTranscript()\n     -> runTracker.finalize()\n     -> server.close()\n```\n\n**Autonomous mode:**\n```\nsuper-ralph reverse \"build a Calendly clone\"\n  -> reverse.ts::runAutonomous()\n     -> PhaseCallbacks:\n          setup: loadTemplate, create outputDir, loadSkill\n          nextIteration: getCurrentSpec() (reads latest .md in outputDir)\n                         -> resolveModel() -> renderPrompt(reverse.hbs, vars)\n                         -> returns PhaseIteration\n          handleResult: returns false if phase_done\n     -> runPhaseLoop() [standard engine path]\n        each iteration: fresh OpenCode session, agent analyzes input, writes/refines spec file\n        agent signals task_complete(\"complete\") until spec is ready, then \"phase_done\"\n```\n\n### Pipeline 2: Decompose (spec -> beads)\n\n```\nsuper-ralph decompose --spec tasks/auth-spec.md --epic-title \"Auth Rebuild\"\n  -> decompose.ts::runDecompose()\n     -> PhaseCallbacks:\n          setup: loadTemplate(\"decompose.hbs\")\n                 runBr([\"create\", \"--type\", \"epic\", \"--title\", title, \"--json\"])\n                 -> epicId (e.g., \"bd-001\")\n          nextIteration: readFileSync(specPath)\n                         getAllBeads(epicId) -> calls br show + br list\n                         resolveModel([]) -> default model\n                         renderPrompt(decompose.hbs, {specContent, epicId, existingBeads, includeReview...})\n          handleResult: false if \"phase_done\", true if \"complete\"\n     -> runPhaseLoop() [engine]\n        each iteration: agent reads spec + existing beads, creates next bead via br create\n        loop continues until agent signals phase_done (all spec requirements covered)\n```\n\n### Pipeline 3: Forward (beads -> code)\n\n```\nsuper-ralph forward --epic bd-001\n  -> forward.ts::runForward()\n     -> PhaseCallbacks:\n          setup: getAllBeads(epicId) -> count for maxIterations (beads.length * 2)\n                 loadTemplate(\"forward.hbs\")\n          nextIteration: getAllReady(epicId) -> calls br ready --parent --json --sort hybrid\n                         if no ready beads: check getEpicProgress -> return null (done)\n                         picked = readyBeads[0] (highest priority)\n                         getBeadDetails(picked.id)\n                         readRecentProgress(projectDir, 5)\n                         resolveModel(bead.labels, bead.title, config, override)\n                         renderPrompt(forward.hbs, {epicId, beadId, beadTitle, ...})\n          handleResult: false if \"phase_done\", true otherwise\n     -> runPhaseLoop()\n        each iteration: fresh session, agent implements bead, runs quality gates,\n                        commits, closes bead via br close, signals task_complete\n```\n\n### SSE Streaming Inner Loop (`opencode.ts::runPrompt`)\n\n```\nv2Client.event.subscribe() -> AsyncIterator<SSE events>\nv2Client.session.promptAsync({ sessionID, model, parts, system })\n  [agent begins processing in OpenCode server, events flow via SSE]\n\nEvent loop (Promise.race between next event and 10s tick):\n  \"tick\" events:\n    - idleFor >= inactivityTimeoutMs (180s default) -> throw Error -> best-effort abort\n    - idleFor >= 30s heartbeat -> log \"[heartbeat] session active, Ns idle\"\n  \n  \"message.part.delta\" (sessionID matches):\n    - field=\"text\": StreamCapture.addDisplayText(delta) + stdout.write(delta)\n  \n  \"message.part.updated\" (sessionID matches):\n    - part.type=\"tool\": StreamCapture.addDisplayText(toolStatusText) + stdout.write\n  \n  \"session.idle\" (sessionID matches):\n    - stdout.write(\"\\n\"), break\n  \n  \"session.error\" (sessionID matches):\n    - print error, break\n\nAfter loop: stream.return() to close SSE connection\n\nPost-processing (v1 client):\n  client.session.messages({path: {id: sessionId}})\n    -> scan all parts for task_complete tool call -> CompletionResult\n    -> sum cost and tokens from assistant message info\n  client.session.diff({path: {id: sessionId}})\n    -> list of changed file paths\n\nReturn PromptResult { completion, cost, tokens, filesChanged, rawOutput, displayOutput }\n```\n\n### Output Capture (`output-parser.ts::StreamCapture`)\n\nMaintains two separate string buffers:\n- `raw` — newline-joined JSON of every SSE event seen (`addRawLine`)\n- `display` — only human-readable text and tool status lines (`addDisplayText`, `toolStatusText`)\n\nBoth are capped at 250,000 characters (truncates from the beginning, adds `... [truncated] ...` marker). Both are written to iteration transcript files by `RunTracker`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. The Plugin System\n\nThe `task_complete` tool is the critical inter-process communication mechanism between the super-ralph orchestrator and the OpenCode agent:\n\n**`/.opencode/plugins/super-ralph.js`:**\n```javascript\nimport { tool } from \"@opencode-ai/plugin\";\nexport default async (ctx) => ({\n  tool: {\n    task_complete: tool({\n      description: \"Signal task/iteration completion. MUST be called as the final action.\",\n      args: {\n        status: tool.schema.enum([\"complete\", \"phase_done\", \"blocked\", \"failed\"]),\n        reason: tool.schema.string().optional(),\n      },\n      async execute(args) {\n        return `Task marked as ${args.status}${args.reason ? \": \" + args.reason : \"\"}`;\n      },\n    }),\n  },\n});\n```\n\nOpenCode discovers this plugin because it lives in `.opencode/plugins/` within the project directory. When an agent session is created for this project, the `task_complete` tool is available. The engine extracts the completion by scanning `session.messages()` for `part.type === \"tool\" && part.tool === \"task_complete\" && part.state.status === \"completed\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Error Handling Strategies\n\nThree configurable strategies (set in `config.engine.strategy`):\n\n| Strategy | Behavior on failure |\n|---|---|\n| `\"retry\"` (default) | Decrement iteration counter, retry up to `max_retries` times, then fall through to skip |\n| `\"skip\"` | Increment `failed`, continue to next iteration |\n| `\"abort\"` | Increment `failed`, break the loop immediately |\n\nFailure statuses that trigger strategy: `\"failed\"`, `\"stalled\"`, `\"timeout\"`, `\"error\"`.\n\nTimeout is two-layered:\n1. `withTimeout(runPrompt(...), timeout_minutes * 60000)` — hard wall clock timeout per iteration\n2. Inactivity watchdog inside `runPrompt` — no SSE events for `inactivity_timeout_seconds` seconds\n\nBoth result in thrown errors caught by the engine's per-iteration try/catch.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Testing Architecture\n\n**Unit tests** (`tests/unit/*.ts`): Run with `bun test`. Cover:\n- `run-state.ts` — `startRunTracker` artifact creation, event recording, transcript writing, finalization\n- `run-status.ts` — reading back run artifacts, resolving \"latest\"\n- `interactive.ts` — mock answer loading/matching for automated interactive session testing\n\n**E2E tests** (`tests/e2e-*.sh`): Shell scripts. Support `--dry-run` (no server needed) and `--live` (requires running OpenCode). Cover all three phases plus `doctor`. Use `mktemp` for isolated project directories and `br` CLI for fixture setup.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Single universal loop engine** — `runPhaseLoop` is the only loop. All three phases are callback implementations, not separate loops. This ensures consistent error handling, timeouts, event emission, and artifact writing everywhere.\n\n2. **Fresh context per iteration** — Each iteration creates a new OpenCode session (new context window). The orchestrator carries state (via beads, spec files, progress.md), not the agent. This is the anti-context-rot mechanism.\n\n3. **task_complete as the sole completion signal** — Session \"idle\" alone is not enough. The agent must call `task_complete`. This ensures intentional signaling and prevents accidental loop continuation on stalled agents.\n\n4. **Ephemeral server by default** — `createOpencode({ port: 0 })` spawns a server on a random port for each run and closes it when done. `--attach <url>` allows reusing an existing server (e.g., for TUI visibility with `opencode attach`).\n\n5. **br CLI as the single source of truth for task state** — Super-ralph never writes to `.beads/` directly. All bead operations go through `Bun.spawn([\"br\", ...])`. The agent also uses `br` directly during forward/decompose.\n\n6. **Handlebars templates are project-owned** — Templates live in `.super-ralph/*.hbs` in the project, not in the CLI. This lets teams customize prompts without modifying the framework. The CLI only supplies defaults via `super-ralph init`.\n\n7. **Area-based model routing** — Beads carry semantic `area:` labels. The config maps areas to models. This decouples task semantics (what kind of work) from model selection (which AI to use), and allows routing without re-creating beads.\n</task_result>",
